<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Distaff" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Distaff,</orth> the staff from which the flax is drawn in spinning: <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 17</bibl>. <cit><quote>could have turned a d. to a lance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 3, 34</bibl></cit>, i. e. women to men.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>